## Name of Session:
disrupting your perspective: become an (secret) agent of disruption

## Session Description 

(Why should students come to this session): Are you interested in biological enhancement? Drop in to learn about biohacking.

## Session Outcomes

quote ghandi and yoda

sell the benefit of disrupting your perspective, not pushing a certain perspective



(What will students learn/leave with?): 

## Session Outline 



count attendees as they walk into room, divide them into groups that way immediately!!!

who do you like to watch lose?(10 min)

introduce ourselves and something that makes us uncomfortable(3 min)

have attendees talk about something that makes them uncomfortable in their groups. everyone will share.(10 min)

show short clip of someone else talking about it(5 min)

go into potential positives of disrupting perspective(10 min)

-sparks innovation

-causes growth(thor rag scene?)

-Can contribute to empathy(or make you realize you don't understand)

-Bring up confucian idea of no true self(https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/apr/09/forget-mindfulness-stop-trying-to-find-yourself-start-faking-it-confucius)

-Bring up agent of disruption article(https://medium.com/@johnsonwhitney/disrupt-yourself-5-ways-to-become-your-own-agent-of-disruption-77d7e2a9d16c)

exercises for disrupting perspective(15 min)

-pick one strategy for disruption from agent of disruption video that they would like to do.

-

wrap up(10 min)




(Please include who is facilitating and how much time you are going to spend in each section):

## Recommended Trajectory 

     Best practices:  No section should be longer than 20 minutes
     Create a session that YOU would want to attend
     Share resources in your slack channel
     All sessions NEED to have a closing activity, reflection, discussion
    
